the Chemical Accident Prevention Provisions (40 CFR 68) is to develop and implement programs to prevent releases of toxic substances and accidents with flammable substances, the federal rule also required that Also Dairy complete analysis of theoretical impacts from catastrophic accidents on the site.  These scenarios were determined by using the EPA's Off-site Consequence Anaysis Guidance document.

Saputo has not had an accident with ammonia in the last five years that requires reporting under this rule.

Saputo has demonstrated their commitment to minimize the potential for accidental releases and thus protect their employees, neighbors, and the surrounding environment in the following manner:

-Committing significant resources to the training of operation, maintenance, and emergency response personnel;
-Hiring external consultants to provide a high level of program competence;
-Dedicating themselves to the continuous improvement of the prevention program at Saputo to futher minimize the potential for accidents.
